channel.title: Function Input and Output :: Introduction to Web Dev
channel.description: In the introduction to this chapter, we used the metaphor of the function machine , noting that the machine takes input and provides output. This section focuses on the details of these two aspects of function behavior. Return Statements Some functions return values that are useful. In particular, the type conversion functions convert input to the specified data type and return the resultâ€”calling Number("3.14") returns the value 3.14.
